ervational selection effect. These results and the absence\nof isentropic cores in cluster atmospheres are in tension with \"precipitation\"\nmodels, particularly those that assume thermal instability ensues from linear\ndensity perturbations in hot atmospheres. Some and possibly all of the\nmolecular gas may instead have condensed from atmospheric gas lifted outward\neither by buoyantly-rising X-ray bubbles or merger-induced gas motions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Oct 2017 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-21"}
